A man has been charged with public order offences after an incident involving a BBC reporter, police said. Leicestershire police said the man would appear at court on Tuesday morning over the incident, which occurred on Sunday. The force did not disclose his name or age. The BBC journalist Sima Kotecha said she and her team were subjected to alleged “racist and abusive behaviour” while preparing to broadcast from Leicester city centre at the weekend. The segment was cancelled and the incident reported to police. The BBC said: “While preparing to broadcast, our reporter, her production team and guests were subjected to racist and abusive behaviour. “We are appalled by what happened … We will not tolerate racism or abuse of our staff.”